            <h2>About SEJKD</h2>
            <p>Southeast Jeet Kune Do is an athletic club seeking to promote realistic self defense methods, athletic martial arts training, functional fitness, and the overall martial lifestyle. We are the operating chapter of the Jeet Kune Do Athletic Association for the greater Augusta, GA area.</p>
            <p>Established in 2010, our studio began as Superior Self Defense Academy (SSDA), where students trained a variety of self defense systems, as well as Bruce Lee’s Jeet Kune Do. Since that time we have been the CSRA’s leader for realistic self-defense and martial arts.  We are the only academy in Augusta, GA and the CSRA teaching Jeet Kune Do. Jeet Kune Do has been cited as the “ultimate fighting art” by Black Belt magazine and was founded by the late Bruce Lee. At our academy, you will receive training under a direct Bruce Lee lineage.</p>
            <img src="_images/about.jpg" alt="" class="inline left">
            <p>As of late 2015, Sifu Kyle McGahee, who has been teaching at the school for over 5 years, purchased Superior Self Defense Academy. The studio has been renamed the Southeast JKD Athletic Club (Southeast JKD for short) to reflect our focus on Jeet Kune Do exclusively.</p>
            <p>We believe in preserving and spreading the philosophy and training methods used by Sijo Bruce Lee and Guro Dan Inosanto, as well as other masters of various styles of martial arts. We teach the arts of Jeet Kune Do and Filipino Kali, as well as incorporate techniques and strategies from Brazilian Jiu Jitsu, Kina Mutai, MMA, Boxing, Savate &amp; Muay Thai to promote health, wellness, and practical self-defense skills.</p>
            <p>Our goal is to help our members develop a strong character, a healthy body, and a peaceful mind. The training is suitable for all ages, as the learning environment is both safe and friendly.</p>
