<section class="cf">
   <h2>Meet Your Coach: Sifu Kyle McGahee – Chief Instructor</h2>
    <p>Sifu Kyle McGahee is the owner and chief instructor of the Southeast Jeet Kune Do Athletic Club, where he spends his time training and coaching students of all ages and backgrounds. He graduated with honors from Augusta State University with a Bachelor’s in Psychology, and is receiving his Master’s of Science in Organizational Psychology in 2016.</p>
    <p>Kyle has made it his goal to build quality students, as well as helping them to open their eyes to new possibilities and free them from their own limitations. He trains each one to develop confidence, self-belief, and character through various methods that come from generations of World Class instructors in Jeet Kune Do, Filipino martial arts (Kali, Escrima, Arnis), Wing Chun, Brazilian Jiu Jitsu, Boxing, Kickboxing, Muay Thai, Savate, and combat Hapkido. These methods, as well as his educational background in psychology, help to deliver the most important and functional aspects of these martial arts styles to beginners and experts alike.</p>
    
