<section><h2>Mission Statement</h2>
    
    <p>The mission of the Jeet Kune Do Athletic Association is to “preserve and perpetuate the Jeet Kune Do way of life.” As the Southeast chapter of the Jeet Kune Do Athletic Assocation, we are also dedicated to this mission. By providing world-class instruction, we offer our students the ability to train their body, and their mind, in order to enrich and enhance their lives in all aspects. Our instructors and our students achieve excellence through hard work, discipline and perseverance.  We operate on simple values, such as respect, honor, loyalty, positivity, compassion, modesty and integrity.</p>
    <p>We are sincerely dedicated to the success of our members and students. This is what drives us. It is what we do on a daily basis. We offer low student-instructor ratios, personalized feedback, and an inclusive atmosphere. We operate from a simple belief that our members are our focus, and we provide honest, sincere direction and coaching. At Southeast JKD, you will never walk in and feel like you aren’t welcomed, or are forgotten the moment you sign up.</p>
    <p>To accomplish this, we do not believe you should be required to sign up for long-term contracts, or a 3 year “Black Belt” training commitment. Nor do we believe that you will receive the same level of attention and focus on your goals for $40 per month at some other gym or academy.</p>
    <p>You don’t have to take our word for it. Give us a call. Schedule a time to come by and experience a class. Only then can you decide what is right for you.</p> </section>

